ican Dream\n|\nA flower doesn’t expect love. She is happy with herself. If she gets love, she celebrates.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nt may not be the life you imagined, but it’s your life. You came here for a reason. Is it time for you to go and begin again?\n\n- Doug   Cooper, Outside In\n|\nThe philosophical study of nature endeavors, in the the vicissitudes of phenomena, to connect the present with the past.\n\n- Alexander\n|\nNever pity missionaries; envy them. They are where the real action is -- where life and death, sin and grace, Heaven and Hell converge.\n\n- Robert\n|\nDreams are deformed reflections of ourselves - less stable and more ungraspable than we are, upon which we in our turn assume the right to reflect upon and to determine.\n\n- Roger\n|\nAre you scared? I understand. The first time I saw my reflection in the mirror, even I was frightened by how BIG my reflection was.\n\n- Atsushi\n|\nIf birds did not believe in their ability to fly, the sky would be empty.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nBooks to the ceiling,Books to the sky,My pile of books is a mile high.How I love them! How I need them!I'll have a long beard by the time I read them.\n\n- Arnold\n|\nWomen still dream and hope, pin their emotions on some man who doesn't reciprocate, and end up in confusion.\n\n- Elisabeth Elliot, Passion and Purity\n|\nEvery day I wake up and ask myself, ‘How can I accept myself and others more fully?\n\n- Alaric Hutchinson, Living Peace\n|\nCrying is all right in its way while it lasts. But you have to stop sooner or later, and then you still have to decide what to do.\n\n- C.S. Lewis, The Silver Chair\n|\nA bore or an uggo might manage not to get up anyone's nose, but if a girl's got brains and looks and personality, she's going to piss someone off, somewhere along the way.\n\n- Tana French, Faithful Place\n|\nThe bonds of family bind us up, support us, help us. And they are also a bond from which it is difficult, perhaps impossible to extricate oneself.\n\n- Neil Gaiman, The Wak