tly decapitated.\n\n- Bob\n|\nSilence can be lovely or disturbing, depending on the source.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nSurely even those immune from the world, for the time being, need the touch of one another, or all is lost.\n\n- Eudora Welty, The Collected Stories\n|\nThrough synergy of intellect, artistry and grace came into existence the blessing of a dancer.\n\n- Shah\n|\nDreams, desires, destiny, and difficulties in life make it a magical and meaningful fairytale.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nHow dull it is to pause, to make an end,To rust unburnish’d, not to shine in use!As tho’ to breathe were life!\n\n- Alfred Tennyson, Ulysses\n|\nThe candle glimmers but an hour. The nightLooms in its ancient hunger. Would you knowThe tragedy of human love and need?Gaze on the stars, then on a brother's face!\n\n- George Sterling, The Thirst of Satan: Poems of Fantasy and Terror\n|\nIt is suicide to be abroad. But what it is to be at home, ... what it is to be at home? A lingering dissolution.\n\n- Samuel Beckett, All That Fall and Other Plays for Radio and Screen\n|\nMr. Franz, I think careers are a 20th century invention and I don't want one.\n\n- Jon Krakauer, Into the Wild\n|\nThe bird flying free has no interest in the truth, searching, or looking for a deeper meaning. The bird flying free just 'is' and that is why it is free.\n\n- Princess Mazzaloulou, The Beautiful Dance of Life\n|\nTo be compassionate, you have to forget your own comfort zone and live well because you live beyond yourself.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nMy grandmother started walking five miles a day when she was sixty. She's ninety-seven now, and we don't know where the heck she is.\n\n- Ellen\n|\nWe are all dust passing through the air, the difference is, some are flying high in the sky, while others are flying low. But eventually, we all settle on the same ground.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nDream Song:In the heavens A noise, Like the rustling of the trees.\n\n- Frances Densmore, American I